-- South African Transport Workers May Strike Over New Road Law, News24 says
-- B y   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 2010-11-12T06:26:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-12/south-african-transport-workers-may-strike-over-new-road-law-news24-says.html
South African passenger and freight
transport in the Gauteng province may be disrupted on Nov. 16
because of a protest by a labor union against a new road law,
 News24  reported, citing South African Trade and Allied Workers’
Union General Secretary Zenzo Mahlangu.  Satawu plans to protest against the implementation of the
Administrative Adjudication of Road Traffic Offences Act that
will deduct points off a driver’s license for traffic offenses,
the Johannesburg-based online news agency reported today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Renee Bonorchis  in Johannesburg at 
